        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 9 at 3:05PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 305 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles east of Jonesboro, moving southwest at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Winnfield, Jonesboro, Hodge, North Hodge, Dodson, East Hodge,
Quitman, Sikes, Hudson and Friendship.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
